# Data for a three-dimensional line
fig = plt.figure()
ax = plt.axes(projection='3d')

zline = np.linspace(0, 15, 1000)
xline = np.sin(zline)
yline = np.cos(zline)
ax.plot3D(xline, yline, zline, 'black')

Using matplotlib to plot 3D shapes¶

In [4]:
def f(x, y):
    return np.sin(np.sqrt(x ** 2 + y ** 2))

x = np.linspace(-6, 6, 1000)
y = np.linspace(-6, 6, 1000)

X, Y = np.meshgrid(x, y)
Z = f(X, Y)

fig = plt.figure()
ax = plt.axes(projection='3d')
ax.contour3D(X, Y, Z, 50, cmap='binary')
ax.set_xlabel('x')
ax.set_ylabel('y')
ax.set_zlabel('z');

def f(x, y):
    return np.sin(5*x)*np.cos(5*y)/5

x = np.linspace(-1, 1, 1000)
y = np.linspace(-1, 1, 1000)

X, Y = np.meshgrid(x, y)
Z = f(X, Y)

fig = plt.figure()
ax = plt.axes(projection='3d')
ax.contour3D(X, Y, Z, 50, cmap='binary')
ax.set_xlabel('x')
ax.set_ylabel('y')
ax.set_zlabel('z');

In [11]:
# Helix equation
t = np.linspace(0, 10, 50)
x, y, z = np.cos(t), np.sin(t), t

fig = go.Figure(data=[go.Scatter3d(x=x, y=y, z=z,
                                   mode='markers')])
fig.show()
In [12]:
def f(x, y):
    return 1-abs(x+y)-abs(y-x)
        
x = np.linspace(-6, 6, 100)
y = np.linspace(-6, 6, 100)
X, Y = np.meshgrid(x, y)
Z = f(X, Y)

fig = go.Figure(data=[go.Surface(z=Z, x=X, y=Y)])
fig.update_layout(title='Piramid', autosize=False,
                  width=500, height=500,
                  margin=dict(l=65, r=50, b=65, t=90))
fig.show()

    return 1/(15*(x**2+y**2))
        
x = np.linspace(-0.1, 0.1, 100)

                  width=500, height=500,

def f(x, y):
    return 0.75/np.exp(((x*5)**2)*((y*5)**2))
        
x = np.linspace(-1, 1, 100)
y = np.linspace(-1, 1, 100)
X, Y = np.meshgrid(x, y)
Z = f(X, Y)

fig = go.Figure(data=[go.Surface(z=Z, x=X, y=Y)])

                  width=500, height=500,

def f(x, y):
    return np.sin(10*(x**2+y**2))/10
        
x = np.linspace(-0.8, 0.8, 100)
y = np.linspace(-0.8, 0.8, 100)
X, Y = np.meshgrid(x, y)
Z = f(X, Y)

fig = go.Figure(data=[go.Surface(z=Z, x=X, y=Y)])
fig.update_layout(title='Ripple', autosize=False,
                  width=500, height=500,
                  margin=dict(l=65, r=50, b=65, t=90))
fig.show()
